##He pulled 100,000 masks and drove to the closed city of Wuhan

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

The following article was written by Jin Bin, the seller

Innovative media, part of Zhejiang Newspaper Group, tells the story of Internet characters.

Wang Shencai, 49, who has never been to Wuhan, is on an unfamiliar journey with an uncertain future. He and the Blue Van with the masks will cross Anhui and Jiangxi provinces and enter Hubei, the hardest hit area of the pneumonia epidemic. His destination is the Dongxihu district health bureau in Wuhan, it is only a few miles from the hard hit Hankou Railway Station, the epicenter of the epidemic.

By Kim Bin

Editor | Tuyanfei

On the 1st day of the 12th Lunar Month, just after noon, Wang Shencai, a driver of a Zhongtong express delivery truck in Ningguo, Anhui Province, received a phone call from his manager asking him to send a batch of relief supplies to Wuhan.

Lao Wang was surprised. He had just returned from visiting relatives in the village. "My uncle, my uncle and my aunt haven't left yet. ". "

Not to mention, the destination is Wuhan, is the epidemic area.

The manager did not speak on the other end of the phone. Lao Wang asked, what materials?

"100,000 masks. "

"It's all right, it's only a trip, " Wang said.

Let's go

Early afternoon 3:00, Wang Shen just sat on his big truck, the engine started that moment, he suddenly some nervous.

The big truck that ran more than ten years, big wind and big waves pass through many, this kind of feeling but only SARS that year just had. He was trapped in Ningbo, his car was not allowed to go on the road, "He hid in the hotel for several days, really scared. ". "

Let's go

Early afternoon 3:00, Wang Shen just sat on his big truck, the engine started that moment, he suddenly some nervous.

The big truck that ran more than ten years, big wind and big waves pass through many, this kind of feeling but only SARS that year just had. He was trapped in Ningbo, his car was not allowed to go on the road, "He hid in the hotel for several days, really scared. ". "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It's a brand-new 9.6-foot car, bought last March, with a range of less than 100,000 miles. Usually, Lao Wang only runs between Ningguo and Wuhu, once a day, and twice a day when he is busy. Last year was busy until twenty-nine, when the last haul was done just after 1 pm.

Lao Wang took care of the car inside and outside, and parked it in the parking space cleanly. He thought, how can we meet this partner after the New Year. I didn't think I'd be leaving soon.

At 5 p.m. , Wang picked up the co-pilot and drove the truck to the warehouse. Two Stevedores loaded 100,000 pairs of masks into his trunk. "It's a big warehouse. "

The donor of the 100,000 pairs said the masks were imported from Japan and were of very high quality, "all N100. ". "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When the bill of sale was signed, Wang Shen suddenly remembered that he had only brought some food and a piece of clothing with him when he went out. He forgot to put on a mask. He asked the warehouse for a few, hung one on his ear, and stuffed the rest on the instrument panel.

One of the Stevedores asked him, where is the delivery?

Lao Wang didn't hide it either, saying it was for Wuhan.

The stevedore said, "Oh, " and took half a pack of cigarettes from his pocket and thrust it at him. Go over there and be careful.

Wang glanced at the time, just past 6 pm, as he was getting out of Ningguo and onto the highway. He pressed down gently on the gas, the Fukuda truck made a low noise, and the stopwatch slowly turned.

Wang Shencai, 49, who has never been to Wuhan, is on an unfamiliar journey with an uncertain future. He and the Blue Van with the masks will cross Anhui and Jiangxi provinces and enter Hubei, the hardest hit area of the pneumonia epidemic. His destination is the Dongxihu district health bureau in Wuhan, it is only a few miles from the hard hit Hankou Railway Station, the epicenter of the epidemic.

In the car, he thought for a long time, finally decided to tell his wife. The wife just said, "protect yourself. ".

In the car, he thought for a long time, finally decided to tell his wife. The wife just said, "protect yourself. ".

The car is heading for Hubei

Wang Shencai every day will run high-speed, very familiar with the high speed, but this time up, it feels a little different from usual.

"there were fewer cars on the road, more cars, only one or two vans, very few, much less than usual. He usually delivers express mail. He also gets on the highway around 6 or 7 in the evening. "there are many, many fewer big trucks. "

The car is little, the road condition is good, the old Wang in the mind estimated, about eight hours can arrive at Wuhan.

They put some gas in a service area in Xuancheng and ate instant noodles. There, Wang Shencai saw for the first time people wearing masks, "the staff who refuels all wear masks, the people who sell things in the shop, all wear masks. ". " He was used to chatting casually with staff members while waiting for gas, but this time everyone was wearing a mask and, apart from the few words necessary to fill up, "was extremely quiet. "

He had to fill up his tank and get out of there.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The next morning, just after 2 am, Wang Shen saw the border of Hubei Province. He quickly woke up his companion and reminded him to put on a mask.

Strange to say, Wang Shencai, 49, has traveled far and wide in logistics, but has never been to Hubei, which is even his ancestral home.

When he was a teenager, a member of his family from his hometown in Hubei Province came to Ningguo, Anhui Province, and found a branch of Lao Wang's grandfather and father, adding to his family tree. Only then did he learn that his hometown was actually Hubei. His father told him that in the early years when people from Hubei Province came to the south of the Yangtze River, his father followed the elders, carrying a load and walking to Ningguo. His father, who was in his eighties, told him only that his hometown was in Dawu County, Hubei, Hubei. Which city does Dawu belong to? "Wang Shen thought for a long time, but did not remember.

In fact, when Wang Shencai's truck was going at full speed to Hubei, his hometown, the COVID-19 of Dawu County, Xiaogan City, Hubei Province, issued a public notice saying that it was very difficult to purchase prevention and control materials and that it openly accepted charitable donations, the required materials include medical masks, protective clothing, shoe covers, medical latex gloves, medical isolation clothing, medical disinfectant and so on.

4:00 a.m. , the van gets off the highway, gets pulled over at the exit.

Looking at the distance beckoning to pull over, with protective clothing armed traffic police, the two men in the cab simultaneously held breath. It wasn't fear, it was just the feeling that we were finally at the place where the outbreak was really bad. "

Before getting off the bus, the co-pilot dropped a sentence: "will we be quarantined as soon as we get back to Ningguo? "? "

In the middle of the night in Wuhan

Wuhan under the rain is not small, very cold.

At the top of the highway, the mouth was eerily quiet, no one was driving, and the distant warning lights flashed and flashed, giving a slight sense of the tension and unease that hung over the city.

A traffic policeman wearing a mask and a hat and a yellow protective suit, like a raincoat, came to inquire and, knowing that it was a mask courier, quickly registered, issued a special pass and let it pass. Before leaving, the other side with them said "hard" , Wang Shen only for the first time on the traffic police have a good impression.

The 9.6-meter truck made a beeline for Wuhan's main city, perhaps the only time it has had the good fortune to drive on a major thoroughfare in a major city.

He slowed his car down and drove it with great care, occasionally pressing it against the manhole cover and making noises that would give him a shock. He looked through the window to make sure it was closed, and then he felt a little more secure.

But they soon got lost in the empty streets.

In the unexpected extra hour or so, Wang Shencai and his companions, "it's impossible not to be nervous. " Both of them are silently watching the city, which has already maxed out the whole country. There were very few cars, no people on the road, the supermarket was open, they saw a few sanitation workers, in the rain sweeping the floor, all wearing masks.

At this point, a colleague driving a van got through to him on the phone and said, "why are you still going in when everyone else is running out? "? "

Wang Shen just told him, the car has arrived in Wuhan, "not so serious feeling outside Ah, are very common. ". "

At a little after 4:00 a.m. , the van arrived at the pickup point.

From the Wuhan Emergency Command Center Office to greet them. Wang Shencai and his colleagues suddenly became nervous and took a step back. "Even the security guard was wearing a tight mask. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The forty-something, bespectacled officer shouted to a group of colleagues as he told them how hard he was working, and quickly removed the mask from the van.

Wang Shencai knew at this time that the mask he pulled was the first item sent to Wuhan by the "Green Channel of Wuhan Relief Materials" organized by the rookie network.

On January 25, Cainiao joint domestic and international logistics enterprises announced the official opening of domestic and global green channel, free from all over the world for the Wuhan region to transport social donations of relief supplies. Each donation organization may dial the CAINIAO Wuhan Material Donation Free Transportation Hotline 400-900-5656 to contact.

Just 16 hours after the green channel was announced, as of 10 a.m. on January 26, hundreds of businesses, organizations and groups around the world had called to contact them for donations, the relief materials involved include masks, test kits, goggles, protective clothing, latex gloves, disinfectant, hydrogen peroxide, lighting equipment and so on.

Donations not only from domestic donors, overseas donors including the United States, the United Kingdom, Japan, South Korea, Thailand, the Philippines, Dubai's corporate donations, public donations, fund-raising donations, international students and so on.

Wang took the time to send his wife a message, tell her, "nothing, very good, very safe, can return immediately. ". "

Persona non grata

As soon as 100,000 masks arrived in Wuhan, Wang's mission was over, but for him, there were plenty of predictable scenarios ahead.

When he was still on his way back, he had already received five or six phone calls from relatives and friends. "I asked if the situation in Wuhan was as serious as they said on TV. I said it was nothing. It was no big deal. ". "

Wang Shen just understood their uneasiness. A truck driver returning from Wuhan can not fail to be the focus of attention at this moment of panic.

Someone from the village has sent a message to him not to go home, and then go back when the epidemic is under control. They are all neighbors of the village. "I say, if you have not been there to see it, you will know that it is not so serious, but that you are afraid of death. However, Wang said he expected to be isolated at home for some time to come.

"To Wuhan to deliver goods, that is one party in trouble, eight sides support. Back home. Got Ta think of the folks back home. "
